      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_fw_upd_1acbfb668d7b4cfa39aa1a5a5dac3c0e7e" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void task</definition>
        <argsstring>(void)</argsstring>
        <name>task</name>
        <reimplements refid="class_task_1a1951102653a5e603f2131b33d7636232">task</reimplements>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Firmware update task function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>Initially the task function calls function boot_write_img_confirmed provided by the MCUboot API. This marks the currently running image as confirmed, which will install it permanently, preventing MCUboot from reverting it for an older image at the next reset. <linebreak/>
 Afterwards the function fota_download_init, provided by the FOTA download library of the nRF Connect SDK, will be called to initialize the firmware over-the-air download library. <linebreak/>
 The function than enters the endless loop and wait for messages. Task wakes up when a message is in the mailbox and read the message by calling mailbox read method which returns the pointer pElem to the message. All expected messages will be handled, in case of an unexpected message an error debug message will be triggered. Finally the message will be released by calling class <ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref> method free, if the pointer pElem is not explicitly set to 0. <linebreak/>
 <linebreak/>
<bold>Message Handling:</bold> <linebreak/>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>eFwInfo: The function allocates an object of type <ref refid="class_fw_info" kindref="compound">FwInfo</ref> and call its method parse to parse the JSON string and to extract the download parameters. To check the validity of the parameters method validate will be called. It extracts the size of the firmware binary and the sha1 checksum and write to download library with call of function fota_download_set_expected provided by the FOTA download library ofthe nRF Connect SDK. With a call of method splitUrl of the <ref refid="class_fw_info" kindref="compound">FwInfo</ref> instance the received URL will be split into host (the http server to download from) and filename (File to request in download) and both will be stored in the member variables hostname and filename by calling the appropriate setter functions. Finally the download will be started by calling the member function download_start.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eFwDownload: Download will be retried because of a previous failure by calling the member function download_start. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
