        <name>download_start</name>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Function to start the OTA download process. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>The function start the OTA download process by calling function fota_download_start provided by the FOTA download library of the nRF Connect SDK. Function fota_download_start start downloading the given file from the given host. When the download is complete, the secondary slot of MCUboot is tagged as having valid firmware inside it. The completion is reported through an event (see fota_dl_handler). In case of an error, indicated by a return value unequal to 0, the member function download_failed will be called. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
